<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1442088>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Discorhabdella pseudaster n. sp., A, habitus of holotype (arrow). B, large subtylostyle. C, tylostyle. D, pseudoastrose acanthotyle. E, immature pseudoastrose acanthotyle. F, pseudoastrose acanthotyle seen from the tip. G, H & I, pseudoasters. J, unguiferous cleistochelae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1442088/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1442090>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Discorhabdella pseudaster n. sp. A, head of a subtylostyle, showing the axial canal. B, head of a pseudoastrose acanthotyle viewed by the top." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1442090/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

